The table also provides average metrics such as the number of tokens in issue descriptions, lines of code modified in fix patches, number of hunks (changesets), and number of files involved.  Key metrics focusing on test result transitions are included, showing the average counts of "Any→PASSED→FAILED→PASSED" unit tests, providing insights into the robustness and reliability of the dataset's annotations. This detailed breakdown allows for a thorough understanding of the characteristics and complexity of the Multi-SWE-bench dataset, facilitating a more robust analysis of the results obtained from the LLM evaluation.
